# role.word — what a ROLE is, a composite word. Descends from word.word, can.word, being.word,
# space.word, and the verbs. The host registry is seed/present/roles/registry.js. A role composes
# from words already grounded, no new primitive. Its can is the granted words grouped by verb
# (canSee, canDo collapse into the verbs). Its voice is the prompt, worn not granted. Its scope is
# the space it is given on, and all under it. roleflow, when a being may play a role, comes next.

A role is a composite word, a can of words.
A role has a name, its handle.
A role's can is words to see, do, call, be, and recall, each word for its verb.
A role has a voice, the manner a being takes in it, no word it can.
A role is given on a space, and its words can there and under it. Its reach may widen this to other paths or narrow it, by path.
A role is granted to a being whole, by its name, at a space or a being.
Roles stack. A being granted many has the words of all.
A being granted a role acts by its words within the role's space, and has it as it moves.
